# Environment Variables for Production Deployment

## Required Environment Variables

### Database (Automatically set by Vercel Postgres)
# These are automatically populated when you add Vercel Postgres storage
# No manual configuration needed!
POSTGRES_URL=""
POSTGRES_PRISMA_URL=""
POSTGRES_URL_NO_SSL=""
POSTGRES_URL_NON_POOLING=""
POSTGRES_USER=""
POSTGRES_HOST=""
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=""
POSTGRES_DATABASE=""

## Optional Environment Variables

### OpenAI Integration (Optional)
# If you want to use real OpenAI API for enhanced categorization
# Leave blank to use rule-based categorization (works well for most cases)
# OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."

### Next.js Configuration
# NODE_ENV is automatically set by Vercel
# NODE_ENV="production"

## Local Development Only
# For local development, you can use a local PostgreSQL database
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@localhost:5432/expenses"
